claim.claim-text:
11. A method for metering fluid flow through a fluid supply line, said method comprising:
providing a flow meter for measuring fluid flow through the supply line, said flow meter having a minimum measuring flow threshold;
providing a valve having an inlet port and an outlet port;
measuring consumed flow rates, exclusive of use of an accumulator for boosting fluid flow through the valve, which are above the minimum measuring flow threshold, or
imparting the supply line with a flow pattern having a pulsating character in which said valve is adapted either to prohibit fluid flow to the fluid supply line until a pressure differential over the valve ports is being built due to consumed flow rates, which are below the measuring flow threshold or to admit fluid flow into the supply line until the pressure differential diminishes below a predetermined threshold;
measuring the fluid flow with admitting thereof.
